Room.Name: The Dragon Sea
Room.Description: There is a certain unrest to the sea here. The waves seem choppier, the clouds darker. A foul wind blows from the east as you hear a clap of thunder coming from that direction.

Room.Name: The Dragon Sea
Room.Description: The sea seems calm enough, but something is amiss. The winds blow a little harder, and the waves slap your craft with a loud clap. You see a dark storm to the east. To the west, you can make out the towers of New Thalos.

Room.Name: The Dragon Sea
Room.Description: The winds blow swiftly from the east, buckling you r boat a little. Though it is still a little calm, a dark storm is brewing east of here, in the direction of Arkham. The waters seem navigable to the west.

Room.Name: The River Delta
Room.Description: The river delta is a maze of waterways, a delta of slow-moving channels and stagnant pools. The water is murky and brown, heavy with sediment from the river that feeds it. The delta is surrounded by lush greenery, with towering trees and dense underbrush providing habitat for a wide range of wildlife. The air is thick with the sound of the river's flow and the calls of birds and other animals. You can see alligators sunning themselves on the banks, while schools of fish swim lazily in the deeper pools. The delta is a peaceful, verdant landscape, where the river flows out into the sea, its water nourishing the fertile land and providing a rich habitat for countless species of flora and fauna.

Room.Name: In the Harbor
Room.Description: You are on the clear blue seas of the Dragon Sea. Water extends in all directions as far as the eye can see. Off in the distance you think you might see a small dock to the south.

Room.Name: The Dragon Sea
Room.Description: The ocean spreads out before you, its surface calm and glassy within the shelter of the harbor. The water is a brilliant shade of blue, reflecting the sky above like a mirror. The harbor is bustling with activity, its waters dotted with boats of all sizes, from small fishing vessels to massive cargo ships. The docks are lined with fishermen mending their nets, while crates of freshly caught seafood are being loaded onto waiting carts. The air is thick with the sound of ropes creaking against masts, seagulls crying overhead, and the calls of sailors as they go about their work. Beyond the harbor, the ocean widens and deepens, its rolling waves crashing against the distant coastline.

Room.Name: The Dragon Sea
Room.Description: The vast ocean is a seemingly endless expanse of blue, stretching as far as the eye can see. The surface of the water is dotted with whitecaps, whipped up by the wind, and the distant horizon is hazy with sea spray. The air is heavy with the scent of salt and seaweed, and the sound of the waves crashing against the shore is a constant background hum. The ocean is alive with activity, from schools of dolphins and whales playing on the surface to schools of fish swimming below. Seabirds wheel overhead, searching for food.

Room.Name: The Dragon Sea
Room.Description: The vast ocean is a seemingly endless expanse of blue, stretching as far as the eye can see. The surface of the water is dotted with whitecaps, whipped up by the wind, and the distant horizon is hazy with sea spray. The air is heavy with the scent of salt and seaweed, and the sound of the waves crashing against the shore is a constant background hum. The ocean is alive with activity, from schools of dolphins and whales playing on the surface to schools of fish swimming below. Seabirds wheel overhead, searching for food.

Room.Name: On a Reef
Room.Description: The shallow reef is a vibrant and colorful landscape, teeming with life. The water is crystal clear, allowing you to see the rocky formations below. Coral formations of every hue, from vibrant pinks and purples to electric blues and greens, form intricate gardens that are home to schools of brilliantly colored fish. Schools of shimmering fish dart in and out of the coral formations, while larger fish, like sea turtles and rays, glide gracefully through the shallows.

Room.Name: The River Delta
Room.Description: The river delta is a maze of waterways, a delta of slow-moving channels and stagnant pools. The water is murky and brown, heavy with sediment from the river that feeds it. The delta is surrounded by lush greenery, with towering trees and dense underbrush providing habitat for a wide range of wildlife. The air is thick with the sound of the river's flow and the calls of birds and other animals. You can see alligators sunning themselves on the banks, while schools of fish swim lazily in the deeper pools. The delta is a peaceful, verdant landscape, where the river flows out into the sea, its water nourishing the fertile land and providing a rich habitat for countless species of flora and fauna.

Room.Name: On a Reef
Room.Description: The shallow reef is a vibrant and colorful landscape, teeming with life. The water is crystal clear, allowing you to see the rocky formations below. Coral formations of every hue, from vibrant pinks and purples to electric blues and greens, form intricate gardens that are home to schools of brilliantly colored fish. The reef is alive with activity, the sound of the waves gently lapping against the rocks blending with the soft rustle of the underwater currents. Schools of shimmering fish dart in and out of the coral formations, while larger fish, like sea turtles and rays, glide gracefully through the shallows.

Room.Name: On a Reef
Room.Description: The shallow reef is a vibrant and colorful landscape, teeming with life. The water is crystal clear, allowing you to see the rocky formations below. Coral formations of every hue, from vibrant pinks and purples to electric blues and greens, form intricate gardens that are home to schools of brilliantly colored fish. The reef is alive with activity, the sound of the waves gently lapping against the rocks blending with the soft rustle of the underwater currents. Schools of shimmering fish dart in and out of the coral formations, while larger fish, like sea turtles and rays, glide gracefully through the shallows.

Room.Name: The Dragon Sea
Room.Description: The ocean stretches out before you, its rolling waves breaking against the coastline in a steady rhythm. The water is a deep, rich blue, its surface shimmering in the sunlight. The ocean is vast and endless, its surface seeming to reach to the horizon and beyond.
